{
  "stem": "1858.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Everyone knows of Auschwitz, but in that period of time, in 1942, in the summer, we did not even know that such a place exists.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And today I wonder about the Nazi guards.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They knew where they are sending us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Because there were close to 8,000 people that we're going to be shipped to Auschwitz-- over 8,000-- they placed us in two buildings where we would have to wait our turn.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And somehow, we were fortunate because we managed to escape.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In that chaos, my mother and my younger sister were separated from my father and me and they ended up in two-- we ended up in two different buildings.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But my father and I managed to escape with the help of a militia man-- that means a Jewish policeman who worked for the Judenrat.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He was a boarder in our house, for when the Nazis entered we had to give a part of our home up and share it with other families.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And since he knew us very well and since he lived in our home, he helped us escape.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He took us in the middle of the night, my father and myself, to the roof of the building, and from there he told us, you will have to go through several buildings, but be careful, and you will make it safely home.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--to another, yes, and we made it safely home.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We immediately tried to inquire of the whereabouts of my mother and my younger sister, and when we found in which building she was, she too was helped by our family physician, Dr.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Plavner, who was a neighbor of ours, who helped them escape in garbage vans.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So here our family was reunited by that time, again--",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
